  "texts": [
    "For the perturbation part, by the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality we haveΩ f θ (x, t) -V[p θ t](x, t) • ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) p θ t (x) dx ≤ 1 12Cσ Ω ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) 2 p θ t (x) dx + 3Cσ Ω f θ (x, t) -V[p θ t](x, t) 2 p θ t (x) dx.",
    "For the interaction part, there are two cases 1 and 2 for the interaction kernel K. We discuss each case respectively.",
    "(Bounded interaction) By the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality we haveΩ Ω K(x -y)(p θ t (y) -pt(y)) dy • ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) p θ t (x) dx ≤ 1 12Cσ Ω ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) 2 p θ t (x) dx + 3Cσ Ω (K * (p θ t -pt))(x) 2 p θ t (x) dx ≤ 1 12Cσ Ω ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) 2 p θ t (x) dx + 3Cσ(C K) 2 Ω |p θ t (y) -pt(y)| dy 2 ≤ 1 12Cσ Ω ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) 2 p θ t (x) dx + 6Cσ(C K) 2 D KL (p θ t ∥ pt),where we use the Csiszár-Kullback-Pinsker inequality [41] for the last inequality.",
    "(Biot-Savart interaction) For the Biot-Savart interaction kernel, as noted by [22], it can be written as:K ⊤ = ∇ • U with U (x) = 1 2π -arctan( x 1 x 2) 0 0 arctan( x 2 x 1).We follow the statement in [33,Appendix E.1] to haveΩ Ω K(x -y)(p θ t (y) -pt(y)) dy • ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) p θ t (x) dx ≤ 1 12Cσ Ω ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) 2 p θ t (x) dx + 3Cσ Ω (∇ log pt(x)) ⊤ U * (p θ t -pt)(x) 2 p θ t (x) dx + 4∥U ∥∞ ∇ 2 pt pt ∞ D KL (p θ t ∥ pt) ≤ 1 12Cσ Ω ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) 2 p θ t (x) dx + 3Cσ ∥∇ log pt∥ 2 ∞ ∥U ∥ 2 ∞ Ω p θ t -pt)(x) dx 2 + 4∥U ∥∞ ∇ 2 pt pt ∞ D KL (p θ t ∥ pt) ≤ Ω ∇ log p θ t (x) pt(x) 2 p θ t (x) 12Cσ dx + 6Cσ ∥∇ log pt∥ 2 ∞ ∥U ∥ 2 ∞ + 4∥U ∥∞ ∇ 2 pt pt ∞ D KL (p θ t ∥ pt),we use the Csiszár-Kullback-Pinsker inequality to obtain the last inequality.",
